SUMMARY:[Hike - Beginner] Heber Down
DESCRIPTION:GTA Hiking & Stuff\nHeber Down Conservation is a great spot fo
 r a beginner Hike.\n\nThis is a beginner/intermediate hike. We will stick 
 to mostly flat and paved sections\, although we will be going into the bac
 k trails where there could be mud/snow. We will cover about 8km.\n\n**THIS
  HIKE STARTS AT 9:30AM**\n\nBring a water bottle and dress for the weather
 .\n\nParts of the trail can get muddy/snowy from the snow. Be prepared.\n\
 nWe are going to meet at the Old Cullen Gardens. Intersection Cochrane & T
 aunton.\n\nGo to the back of the parking lot near the new Pickleball court
 s. The path starts to the left of the picnic shelter.\n\n**Hike leaves pro
 mptly at 9:35AM**\n\n**Winter Hiking Season Information:**\n\nPlease note 
 that as we get into winter hiking with snow and slippery trails\, we consi
 der proper Crampons to be mandatory.\nThe event host can ask you not to pa
 rticipate if you don't have proper footwear including Crampons. More [Cram
 pon Information](https://www.meetup.com/gta-hiking-meetup/events/297067178
 /).\n\n**LEGAL DISCLAIMER AND LIABILITY INFORMATION:**\n\nBy RSVP'ing and 
 paying the event fee (if applicable)\, you are confirming that you have re
 ad\, understand and accept the following:\n\n1. **GTA Hiking Meetup is a p
 rivate group**. Attending events is voluntary by you as a member. Particip
 ation in any activity with us is at your own risk.\n2. By joining this eve
 nt as a member you agree to indemnify and hold harmless its organizers\, c
 o-organizers\, assistant organizers\, event hosts\, and other members from
  all claims or liability of every type (including court costs and legal fe
 es) for injury or death to any person or for damage to property\, loss of 
 personal property or any other wrongful act arising out of or relating to 
 your participation as a member. This agreement applies to you and to other
  persons (as your guests) who may accompany you in these endeavors.\n3. Yo
 u also agree to hold the organizers as well as other group members harmles
 s. By participating voluntarily in the group\, you expressly waive any and
  all such claims against each and every other member in the group\, includ
 ing without limitation any and all claims against the group organizer\, co
 -organizers\, assistant organizers\, and event hosts.
